###  this tools function ###

usage:
 [tools] [option] [files]

 option:
	 -l [m,n]		:    list ts-pkgs header info , from m to n. default list first 5 ts header info
						 if n not set, will only print m pkgs info.
						 if have video,print I/B/P frame type ,and a/v's time.
	 -off hex       :    print 'hex' position or near-after positon's ts-pkg header info
						 if have video,print I/B/P frame type ,and a/v's time.
	 -pat           :    print pat ts-info
	 -pmt           :    print pmt ts-info
	 -media         :    print a/v info (codec,h/w)



